%N A396158 Triangle; T(n,m) is the number of possible outcomes having a run of m or more sixes when a die is rolled n times.
%C A396158 See also A396157, the number of possible outcomes having a run of m or more heads when a coin is tossed n times.
%F A396158 T(n,m) = A081041(n-m) for ceiling(n/2) <= m <= n.
%F A396158 T(2*n+1,n) = A081041(n+1) - 5.
